Aerodynamic forces were measured using a custom-built, low-speed wind tunnel and a six-component balance. Hoverflies were mounted on a sting, and their bodies were aligned with the freestream flow. Measurements were taken at a Reynolds number of $Re = 10^4$ based on body length.

